article.headline: Temple 85, Saint Louis 79
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Dustin Salisbery scored 25 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Temple snapped a five-game losing streak by beating Saint Louis 85-79 on Wednesday, the Owls' first victory in the Atlantic 10. Dionte Christmas and Mark Tyndale scored 22 points apiece and Dion Dacons had 11 for Temple (7-9, 1-3 Atlantic 10). Tommie Liddell tied his career-high with 28 points, Luke Meyer and Danny Brown added 13 points each and Ian Vouyoukas contributed 11 for Saint Louis (12-6, 2-3). Liddell hit his first eight 3-pointers and finished 8-of-12. The Billikens trimmed Temple's lead to 70-69 on a basket by Brown with 3:13 remaining. But the Owls came right back with eight straight points -- five of them from Tyndale -- to take a 78-69 lead with 2:03 left. Temple led by as many as 13 points in the first half, but the Billikens stayed close thanks to some hot shooting. Saint Louis was 17-of-24 from the field (71 percent), including 8-of-11 from 3-point territory. After the Owls took a 49-40 lead, Saint Louis responded with five points in the final 34.3 seconds of the first half, capped by a 25-foot 3-pointer by Liddell at the buzzer, to make the halftime deficit 49-45.
